OL,7,F"On the wider issue of pre-release
OL,8,Ftesting, prisoners approaching the end
OL,9,Fof their sentence are often tested
OL,10,Fprior to release back into the
OL,11,Fcommunity. Individuals progress by
OL,12,Ffully engaging in a number of tests
OL,13,Fwhich challenge and support them to
OL,14,Fmake positive change in their lives
OL,15,Faround health, thinking patterns and
OL,16,Fattitudes towards their offending
OL,17,Fbehaviour. After being fully risk
OL,18,Fassessed, they begin a graduated
OL,19,Frelease programme into the community,
OL,20,Ffirstly under supervision then
OL,21,Fprogressing to short time bounded
OL,22,Fperiods of unaccompanied release where
OL,23,Fthey work in the community."
